# eliteOS architecture (Cursor)

- **Product name:** Use **eliteOS** in user-facing copy, docs aimed at founders/customers, and new UI strings. Legacy repo identifiers (`eos`, `eOS`, `EOS_*`) may exist until a deliberate rename—do not churn unrelated identifiers without a ticket.
- **Shared Brain:** New heads and features should call **`backend-core`** (or successor API), not introduce parallel sources of truth for the same business entities.
- **No silent tenant coupling:** Avoid hardcoded fabricator-specific IDs, branch names, or shop-only assumptions in shared logic. Prefer org-scoped config (`organization_id`, `organization_integration_configs`, pricing structures).
- **New tenant-owned data:** Prefer **`organization_id`** on new tables/rows or document a narrow exception in `docs/eliteos/FEATURE_DECISIONS.md`.
- **Secrets:** Never put Supabase **service role**, Monday tokens, Moraware credentials, or partner API secrets in frontend code or client env bundles exposed to the browser.
- **Permissions:** Enforce authorization in **backend** code (or Supabase RLS where used)—**never** rely on UI-only hiding for security.
- **Shared topbar:** Every **protected internal head** must use **`shared/eliteos-ui/EliteosTopbar`** for its header shell. Do **not** create one-off local topbars for protected heads. The shared component is purely presentational — it must not import Supabase, call backend APIs, read env vars, own auth/session state, or contain business logic. Each head passes user identity, org data, and sign-out/menu actions through props. **Home Launcher** is the only head that passes the `searchSlot` prop (head finder) unless a new head is explicitly approved to do so. Public/customer-facing heads (e.g. `app-quote`, `app-partner-quote`) may intentionally use different chrome.
- **New protected head scaffold:** Before shipping a new protected head, verify the **new-head checklist** in `docs/eliteos/SYSTEM_BLUEPRINT.md §15`.
- **Living docs:** After meaningful architecture, SaaS, integration, security, deployment, or pricing-flow changes, update **`docs/eliteos/SYSTEM_BLUEPRINT.md`** or **`docs/eliteos/FEATURE_DECISIONS.md`**.
- **Head inventory:** See **`docs/eliteos/eliteOS-master-head-map.md`** before adding a new head.
